  "prompt": "Why do all people start chanting about Chetan Bhagat?",
  "response": "Chetan Bhagat is a popular contemporary Indian author known for his accessible and engaging writing style, which resonates with many readers, particularly younger audiences. His novels often deal with themes related to modern Indian society, youth issues, and romantic relationships, making them relatable to a broad segment of the population. Some reasons why people might start \"chanting\" or discussing Chetan Bhagat could include:\n\n1. **Popularity**: His books have sold millions of copies and many have been adapted into successful Bollywood movies. This makes him a well-known figure in popular culture.\n  \n2. **Relatability**: Bhagat's writing often captures the experiences and aspirations of young Indians, making them feel heard and understood.\n\n3. **Media Presence**: Bhagat is also active in the media, contributing regularly to newspapers, appearing in interviews, and engaging with his audience on social media, which keeps him in public discourse.\n\n4. **Controversy and Debate**: Bhagat's works and his public statements sometimes spark controversy and debate, adding to the attention he receives.\n\nOverall, the combination of his popularity, relevance, and media presence contributes to why people frequently discuss Chetan Bhagat and his works.",
